cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.SY

The paper proposes a methodology of using LSTM-based deep-RNN for time-series prediction, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses recurrent neural network (RNN), which is a type of neural network commonly used in time-series prediction, further supporting the likelihood of cs.LG. The paper also discusses the training and testing of the RNN networks, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of LSTM, which is a type of neural network architecture, suggests the possibility of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a category. The paper also deals with the prediction of two-phase flow regime, which is a topic in control systems and signal processing, indicating the possibility of cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
